BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Free virtual lecture: The Lives and Times of Midwest Amphibians wi
 th Dr. Spencer Cortwright
DTSTART:20260528T190000
DTEND:20260528T203000
UID:98da05f623066c829b7ce3119d223c81@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Each spring amphibians bring great joy as they seem to suddenl
 y emerge from a frozen landscape. Join us for a free virtual lecture and Q
 &amp\;A with Dr. Spencer Cortwright\, Professor of Biology at Indiana Univ
 ersity Northwest and longtime researcher of amphibian and restoration ecol
 ogy. Dr. Cortwright will take us on a richly illustrated journey through t
 he lives of Midwestern amphibians\, exploring their year-round life cycles
 \, seasonal movements\, and the remarkable adaptations that help them tran
 sition from a frozen landscape to springtime abundance.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/the-lives-and-times-of-midwest-a
 mphibians-with-dr-spencer-cortwright/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beanblossom Bottoms 30th Anniversary: Sunrise Yoga with Alex Hodge
DTSTART:20260809T063000
DTEND:20260809T074500
UID:071411eb951d67e4985dd7a244c458e0@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Start your day with a peaceful yoga session in the serene wood
 s of Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve. Breathe in the fresh morning air
 \, move with the rhythm of nature\, and soak in the beauty of sunrise filt
 ering through the trees. Suitable for all levels. Please bring your own ma
 t and water. This event is free to honor the 30th Anniversary of Beanbloss
 om Bottoms Nature Preserve. This event was rescheduled from June 14 due to
  spring flooding. If this event is full\, sign up for the wait list.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/04/beanblossom-bottoms-30th-anniver
 sary-sunrise-yoga-with-alex-hodge/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beanblossom Bottoms 30th Anniversary: Beanblossom Birding with Cat
 hy Meyer
DTSTART:20260809T080000
DTEND:20260809T100000
UID:6279c85a4bf772e1026118008cdbd8f5@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a guided birding hike through the diverse habitats
  of Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve. Listen for songbirds\, watch for 
 soaring raptors\, and catch glimpses of wetland species along the boardwal
 k. All experience levels are welcome. Binoculars are available. Cathy is a
  retired naturalist from Monroe County Parks and Recreation and a member o
 f the Indiana Audubon Society and Sassafras Audubon Society. She led bird 
 hikes for the Indiana Dunes Birding Festival\, Sycamore Land Trust\, and o
 ther groups. This event was rescheduled from June 14 due to spring floodin
 g. If this hike is full\, sign up for the wait list.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/04/beanblossom-bottoms-30th-anniver
 sary-beanblossom-birding-with-cathy-meyer/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beanblossom Bottoms 30th Anniversary: Intro to Botany with Natalie
  Marinova
DTSTART:20260809T090000
DTEND:20260809T110000
UID:6e0e4b7a5775f7d191f356f3c85a97cd@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Curious about plant names and botanical terms? Join us for a b
 eginner-friendly botany class where we’ll break down essential plant ter
 minology and the basics of Latin names. Learn how scientific names reveal 
 plant characteristics\, relationships\, and identification tips. Perfect f
 or nature enthusiasts\, gardeners\, and anyone eager to deepen their plant
  knowledge! Natalie has a deep love and passion for Midwestern native plan
 ts\, and is an owner of Eco Logic LLC and is the Director of Native Landsc
 aping and Green Infrastructure. This event was rescheduled from June 14 du
 e to spring flooding. If this hike is full\, sign up for the wait list.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/04/beanblossom-bottoms-30th-anniver
 sary-intro-to-botany-with-natalie-marinova/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beanblossom Bottoms 30th Anniversary: Botany and Ecology with Tom 
 Swinford
DTSTART:20260809T103000
DTEND:20260809T123000
UID:0c6274cb12d4c0d1490bf329519c9fd1@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a guided hike through Beanblossom Bottoms Nature P
 reserve with Sycamore&#8217\;s Land Preservation Director Tom Swinford\, a
 n expert ecologist and naturalist with over 30 years of experience with th
 e Indiana DNR Division of Nature Preserves and The Nature Conservancy. Dis
 cover the rich natural history of this restored wetland ecosystem as Tom s
 hares insights on the area&#8217\;s geology\, plant communities\, and wild
 life. This leisurely walk will highlight the ecological significance of th
 e preserve and its role in regional conservation efforts. This event was r
 escheduled from June 14 due to spring flooding. If this hike is full\, sig
 n up for the wait list.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/04/beanblossom-bottoms-30th-anniver
 sary-natural-history-of-beanblossom-and-plant-identification-with-tom-swin
 ford/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
